FT  20 OCT 94 / World Stock Markets: Canada
The afternoon rally in New York helped to lift the Toronto market off its
lows to end little changed on the day after moderate trade. The TSE 300
index gained a net 4.83 at 4,320.79 and declines narrowly led rises by 366
to 347 after volume of 54.9m shares valued at CDollars 680m.
Base metal issues rose on strong metal prices. Aluminium is at a four-year
peak and nickel is at its highest for two years. Gold, transportation and
paper stocks also advanced.
